race.comment: HENNESSY LAD (2) sat on the pace and stuck on well to score by a neck this distance last start running his best race since the switch from a smart Victorian yard. Has been kept on the fresh side and can go on with the job. Stablemate AWASH (1) just missed in the same contest racing forward and has a weight swing in his favour. Has the rail and will get every chance to go one better. VIERI (5) improved again winning a 54 by a space. Tumbles in weight and that gives him a chance. KANGAROO COURT (3) led and was beaten 2.3L in the HENNESSY LAD race and will give a sight again. SHAKATTAK (4) is in the right yard but needs to lift to be any threat.
